{"lemma":"قابِض","slug":"قابِض","root":"ق.ب.ض","root_slug":"ق-ب-ض","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ب-ض","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","name","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35108"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%90%D8%B6"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"depressing"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"flexor (causing the joint to flex)","examples":[{"text":"Coordinate term: بَاسِط (bāsiṭ)"},{"text":"عَضَلَة قَابِضَة","english":"a flexor muscle"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"clutch"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"constriction"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"Al-Qabid, \"the Restrainer, the Straightener\" one of the names of God in Islam."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of قَبَضَ (qabaḍa, “to seize”)."},"ipa":["/qaː.bidˤ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35108","headword_ar":"قَابِضٌ","root":"qbD","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Taking with the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in any manner: taking possession of: receiving:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1:)]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grasping, clutching,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seizing, with the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, [but in an intensive sense,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~aADN","text_ar":"قَبَّاضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or the latter is of the dial. of the people of El-Medeeneh, applied to him"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grasps"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collects everything:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-'Othmán El-Mázinee:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qb~aADapN","text_ar":"قبَّاضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which is doubly intensive]; (K;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this last not denoting the fem. gender. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAbiDu AlA^arowaAHi","text_ar":"قَابِضُ الاَرْوَاحِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The taker of the souls"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is an appellation of [the Angel of Death,] 'Izrá-eel, or 'Azrá-eel. (TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaAbiDu","text_ar":"القَابِضُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", one of the names of God, signifies (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Withholder"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Straitener"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Scanter"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the means of subsistence,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of other things,"},{"kind":"text","text":"from his servants, by his graciousness and his wisdom: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the Taker of souls, at the time of death."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  A bird (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contracting his wing to fly."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And hence, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaAbiDN","text_ar":"قَابِضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyDN","text_ar":"قَبِيضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K) A bird, (K,) or horse, (A,) or other [animal], (K,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in flight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in going"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pace:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or a man (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"light,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"active, and quick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) and [hence, app.,] the latter also signifies (assumed tropical:)  an"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"intelligent"},{"kind":"text","text":"man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who keeps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"adheres, to his art,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"work."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ibn-'Abbád, K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ad~i","text_ar":"الشَّدِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabiyDu","text_ar":"قَبِيضُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"A horse, (S, K, in [some of] the copies of the K “ a man, ” which is a mistake, though it seems to be also applied to a man, TA,) or a beast of carriage, (L,) (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quick in the shifting of the legs from place to place"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in running"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, L, K.) ―         -b3-  A camel-driver (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driving quickly; a quick driver;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner, [but in an intensive sense,] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~aADN","text_ar":"قَبَّاضٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and [in a doubly intensive sense] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qab~aADapN","text_ar":"قَبَّاضَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the last signifies (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driving away vehemently;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"denoting intensiveness; and is applied to an ass driving away his she-ass, and to a camel-driver. (M.) [See an ex. of the first, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAy^iDF","text_ar":"عَايِضً"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EwD","text_ar":"عوض"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  [Applied to medicine, food, &c., (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Astringent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"constipating."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["K","TA","S","A","L"]}]}}